2%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20Long%20Island%20City%20and%20Manhattan%20from%20rooftop%2C%20Greenpoint%2C%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634de5d10dfcda409665934%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22915%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInclusionary%20zoning%20is%20designed%20to%20boost%20the%20production%20of%20affordable%20housing%20by%20requiring%20or%20incentivizing%20developers%20to%20build%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20below-market-rate%20units.%3Cp%3ELindsey%20Nicholson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInclusionary%20zoning%20policies%20can%20backfire%2C%20leading%20to%20fewer%20homes%20and%20higher%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20suggests%20ways%20to%20optimize%20inclusionary%20zoning%20for%20affordable%20housing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20direct%20housing%20subsidies%2C%20like%20vouchers%2C%20can%20be%20more%20effective%20and%20flexible.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20policy%20designed%20to%20create%20affordable%20housing%20for%20low-income%20people%20has%20long%20been%20scrutinized%20for%20being%20generally%20ineffective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInclusionary%20zoning%2C%20which%20originated%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20boost%20the%20production%20of%20affordable%20housing%20by%20requiring%20or%20incentivizing%20developers%20to%20set%20aside%20a%20certain%20share%20of%20below-market-rate%20units%20when%20building%20new%20apartments%20or%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20to%20leverage%20land-use%20regulations%20to%20have%20the%20private%20sector%20offer%20some%20homes%20for%20lower-income%20people.%20The%20term%20is%20a%20response%20to%20%26quot%3Bexclusionary%20zoning%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0laws%20like%20single-family%20zoning%20that%20make%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20cheaper%20units%20in%20multi-family%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20which%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2019%2F06%2F18%2Fupshot%2Fcities-across-america-question-single-family-zoning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edominates%20American%20cities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20cements%20racial%20and%20socioeconomic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftcf.org%2Fcontent%2Ffacts%2Funderstanding-exclusionary-zoning-impact-concentrated-poverty%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esegregation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Finclusionary-zoning-hurts-more-it-helps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritics%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20long%20pointed%20out%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.law.yale.edu%2Ffss_papers%2F468%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einclusionary%20zoning%20policies%20often%20backfire%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20raising%20costs%20so%20much%20for%20developers%20that%20they%20cancel%20or%20significantly%20scale%20back%20new%20housing%20projects.%20At%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20more%20inclusionary%20zoning%20requirements%20mean%20less%20affordable%20and%20market-rate%20housing%20is%20constructed%20than%20otherwise%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20advocates%20of%20land-use%20policies%20like%20inclusionary%20zoning%20argue%20that%20any%20additional%20affordable%20housing%20is%20a%20net%20benefit%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20less%20housing%20overall%20or%20higher%20rents.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0094119021000656%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elots%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theurbanist.org%2F2021%2F06%2F02%2Fnew-round-of-studies-underscore-benefits-of-building-more-housing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20restricting%20the%20supply%20of%20housing%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20market-rate%20homes%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0means%20higher%20rents%20and%20home%20prices.%20So%20a%20policy%20designed%20to%20create%20more%20affordable%20housing%20can%20actually%20result%20in%20fewer%20homes%20and%20higher%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%20by%20UCLA%20housing%20researcher%20Shane%20Phillips%20found%20that%20while%20inclusionary%20zoning%20is%20deeply%20flawed%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20design%20the%20policy%20to%20maximize%20its%20benefits.%20Phillips%20used%20a%20simulator%20developed%20by%20UC%20Berkeley's%20Terner%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Innovation%20to%20predict%20how%20much%20both%20market-rate%20and%20low-income%20housing%C2%A0inclusionary%20zoning%20would%20produce.%20He%20looked%20specifically%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanning.lacity.gov%2Fplans-policies%2Ftransit-oriented-communities-incentive-program%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Angeles'%20Transit%20Oriented%20Communities%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20incentivizes%20developers%20on%20a%20voluntary%20basis%20to%20build%20housing%20around%20bus%20and%20train%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhillips%20wanted%20to%20determine%20whether%20there's%20an%20optimal%20inclusionary%20zoning%20policy%20and%20if%20not%2C%20what%20the%20policy's%20tradeoffs%20look%20like.%20This%20involves%20finding%20a%20balance%20between%20creating%20more%20deed-restricted%20affordable%20housing%20and%20boosting%20the%20overall%20supply%20of%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20concluded%20that%20the%20value%20of%20the%20government%20subsidy%20for%20building%20affordable%20housing%20needs%20to%20outweigh%20its%20costs.%20If%20taxes%20are%20too%20high%20on%20new%20construction%2C%20the%20new%20housing%20just%20won't%20go%20up.%20And%20because%20it's%20hard%20to%20strike%20that%20balance%20correctly%20in%20every%20case%2C%20Phillips%20also%20found%20the%20policy%20should%20be%20voluntary%2C%20rather%20than%20mandated.%20That%20way%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20calibrate%20wrong%2C%20if%20you%20require%20too%20much%20and%20offer%20too%20little%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20kill%20projects%20because%20they%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20go%20down%20that%20pathway%2C%26quot%3B%20Phillips%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20possible%20to%20improve%20inclusionary%20zoning%2C%20Phillips%20found%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20policy%20%26quot%3Bare%20very%20likely%20greater%20than%20the%20benefits.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20recognizes%20that%20it%20can%20be%20politically%20impossible%20for%20policymakers%20to%20abandon%20the%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20to%20say%20that%20we%20should%20just%20get%20rid%20of%20these%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20Phillips%20said.%20%26quot%3BPartly%20for%20political%20reasons%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20just%20a%20necessity%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20and%20maybe%20at%20least%20a%20bridge%20to%20something%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudying%20the%20impacts%20of%20inclusionary%20zoning%20is%20increasingly%20important%20because%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20states%20and%20localities%20are%20looking%20to%20boost%20all%20kinds%20of%20infill%20construction%20in%20existing%20neighborhoods%2C%20including%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bmissing%20middle%20housing%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0everything%20between%20a%20detached%20single-family%20home%20and%20an%20apartment%20building.%20While%20larger%20apartment%20buildings%20are%20generally%20better%20able%20to%20absorb%20the%20costs%20of%20inclusionary%20zoning%2C%20it%20often%20doesn't%20pencil%20out%20to%20build%20below-market%20units%20in%20smaller%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20make%20inclusionary%20zoning%20work%20when%20most%20of%20your%20projects%20in%20your%20city%20are%2050%20units%2C%20100%20units%2C%26quot%3B%20Phillips%20said.%20To%20encourage%20the%20construction%20of%20missing%20middle%20housing%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20really%20need%20a%20simple%20process%20and%20minimal%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20policy%20experts%2C%20including%20Phillips%2C%20would%20rather%20see%20governments%20provide%20much%20more%20in%20direct%20housing%20subsidies%2C%20both%20for%20low-income%20people%20and%20homebuilders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDirect%20subsidies%2C%20like%20housing%20vouchers%2C%20give%20low-income%20residents%20more%20flexibility%3A%20they%20can%20choose%20where%20they%20want%20to%20live.%20And%20every%20dollar%20spent%20on%20direct%20housing%20support%2C%20like%20housing%20vouchers%2C%20tends%20to%20go%20farther%20than%20a%20dollar%20used%20to%20subsidize%20the%20construction%20of%20an%20affordable%20unit%2C%20Phillips%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%2C%20over%20time%2C%20need%20to%20move%20away%20from%20trying%20to%20have%20land%20use%20reforms%20serve%20multiple%20purposes%2C%20let%20them%20do%20what%20they're%20good%20for%2C%20which%20is%20producing%20more%20housing%20of%20different%20types%2C%26quot%3B%20Phillips%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20really%20need%20to%20find%20resources%20and%20commit%20resources%20to%20subsidizing%20housing%20for%20people%20who%20can't%20afford%20it%20on%20their%20own%2C%20whether%20through%20vouchers%20or%20subsidies%20for%20construction%2C%20really%20both.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finclusionary-zoning-failing-low-income-residents-affordable-housing-crisis-solution-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714815721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634e59bec0c69656900ab42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finclusionary-zoning-failing-low-income-residents-affordable-housing-crisis-solution-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inclusionary%20zoning%20is%20often%20so%20expensive%20that%20developers%20build%20less%20housing%20overall.%20Making%20it%20voluntary%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20incentives%20generous%20%E2%80%94%20would%20help.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(El