%20last%20year.%20India%20is%20also%20poised%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20third-largest%20economy%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%202%2C%20President%20Biden%20had%20said%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20our%20economy%20is%20growing%20is%20because%20of%20you%20and%20many%20others.%20Why%3F%20Because%20we%20welcome%20immigrants.%20We%20look%20to%20the%20reason%20(behind%20this)...think%20about%20it.%20Why%20is%20China%20stalling%20so%20badly%20economically%3F%20Why%20is%20Japan%20having%20trouble%3F%20Why%20is%20Russia%3F%20Why%20is%20India%3F%20Because%20they're%20xenophobic.%20They%20don't%20want%20immigrants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20President%20said%20this%20while%20campaigning%20for%20his%20re-election%20for%20the%20US%20Presidency%20at%20a%20fundraising%20event%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20claim%20on%20%26quot%3Bxenophobia%26quot%3B%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia%20has%20always%20been%20a%20very%20unique%20country...%20I%20would%20say%20actually%2C%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20world%2C%20that%20it's%20been%20a%20society%20which%20has%20been%20very%20open...%20different%20people%20from%20different%20societies%20come%20to%20India.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20gave%20an%20example%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20more%20popularly%20called%20CAA%2C%20in%20making%20his%20point.%20He%20highlighted%20how%20the%20CAA%2C%20introduced%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20government%2C%20showcases%20India's%20welcoming%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20we%20have%20the%20CAA%20(Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act)%2C%20which%20is%20to%20open%20up%20doors%20for%20people%20who%20are%20in%20trouble...%20I%20think%20we%20should%20be%20open%20to%20people%20who%20have%20the%20need%20to%20come%20to%20India%2C%20who%20have%20a%20claim%20to%20come%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20also%20spoke%20about%20the%20narrative%20created%20by%20a%20section%20of%20the%20western%20media%20and%20backed%20it%20with%20an%20example%20of%20the%20ongoing%20protests%20at%20US%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20spoke%20about%20the%20ongoing%20anti-Israel%20protests%20in%20American%20university%20campuses%20and%20criticised%20a%20section%20of%20the%20Western%20media%20for%20its%20biased%20coverage%2C%20suggesting%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20ideological%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20at%20all%20%26quot%3Bobjective%26quot%3B%20reporting.%20He%20said%20that%20this%20section%20of%20media%20wants%20to%20shape%20the%20global%20narrative%20and%20has%20been%20targeting%20India%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20curb%20the%20diplomatic%20fallout%20of%20President%20Biden's%20remarks%20terming%20India%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20other%20nations%2C%20%26quot%3Bxenophobic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20White%20House%20issued%20a%20clarification%20on%20the%20President's%20intentions%2C%20emphasising%20his%20%26quot%3Brespect%26quot%3B%20for%20allies%20and%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20Press%20Secretary%20Karine%20Jean%20Pierre%20asserted%20that%20the%20President's%20comments%20were%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20message%20emphasising%20the%20strength%20derived%20from%20America's%20immigrant%20heritage.%20She%20stressed%20that%20Biden's%20focus%20remains%20on%20bolstering%20diplomatic%20relationships%20with%20nations%20such%20as%20India%20and%20Japan%2C%20evident%20in%20his%20actions%20over%20the%20past%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20we%20have%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%2C%20India%2C%20with%20Japan%2C%20and%20the%20President%20if%20you%20just%20look%20at%20the%20last%20three%20years%20has%20certainly%20focused%20on%20those%20diplomatic%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3E(Inputs%20from%20ANI)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%