0terrace.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGrow%20your%20own%20fruits%20with%20these%208%20tips%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Place%20the%20fruit%20trees%20strategically%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Jayanti%2C%20urban%20gardeners%20should%20first%20ensure%20a%20proper%20drainage%20system%20on%20the%20terrace%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20absorb%20excess%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSecondly%2C%20keep%20your%20pots%20such%20that%20they%20are%20placed%20above%20the%20beams%20and%20walls%20of%20the%20rooms%20that%20are%20below%20the%20terrace.%20This%20will%20ensure%20that%20the%20weight%20of%20trees%20is%20balanced%20and%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20house%20does%20not%20get%20damaged%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Upcycle%20discarded%20fish%20crates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20large%20pots%2C%20Jayanti%20plants%20fruits%20in%20fish%20crates%20of%2027*17*12%20inches.%20%E2%80%9CI%20purchase%20discarded%20fish%20crates%20at%20lower%20prices%20in%20the%20fish%20market.%20I%20make%20holes%20at%20its%20bottom%20and%20then%20add%20the%20soil%20mixture.%20These%20fish%20crates%20are%20very%20sturdy.%20I%20am%20still%20using%20fish%20crates%20that%20I%20bought%2020%20years%20ago%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Instead%20of%20large%20pots%2C%20Jayanti%20plants%20fruits%20in%20fish%20crates.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525-300x157.jpg%20