0in%20Alwar%2C%20Rajasthan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20architect%20runs%20Sketch%20Design%20Studio%2C%20and%20built%20this%202%2C000%20square%20feet%20home%20using%20natural%20materials%C2%A0%20and%20revived%20ancient%20techniques.%20The%20home%20is%20built%20using%20mud%20and%20earth%20sacks%20along%20with%20lime%20and%20plaster.%20She%20even%20incorporated%20neem%20leaves%2C%20turmeric%20and%20jaggery%20in%20the%20building%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20edibles%20have%20been%20used%20for%20years%20in%20earthen%20constructions%20due%20to%20their%20many%20properties%20%E2%80%94%20neem%20keeps%20termites%20at%20bay%2C%20while%20jaggery%20is%20a%20great%20binding%20material%2C%20and%20methi%20(fenugreek)%2C%20too%2C%20binds%20the%20bricks%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Shipra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20challenge%20was%20designing%20for%20Alwar%E2%80%99s%20extreme%20climate%2C%20with%20temperatures%20going%20from%20as%20high%20as%2041%20degrees%20Celcius%20to%20as%20low%20as%208%20degrees%20Celcius%20in%20the%20winters.%20The%20architect%20designed%20the%20home%20in%20a%20strategic%20manner%20to%20maintain%20a%20comfortable%20climate%20inside%20all%20year-round.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20part%20%E2%80%93%20it%20has%20zero%20cement.%20The%20central%20roof%20at%20a%20height%20of%2023%20feet%2C%20along%20with%20huge%20windsor%2C%20ensures%20proper%20ventilation%20and%20sunlight%20penetration.%C2%A0%20Adding%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F335976%2Fmumbai-sustainable-home-ecofriendly-mud-architecture-geeli-mitti-ngo-lakhichand-jain%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estructural%20sustainability%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20the%20rainwater%20harvesting%20and%20greywater%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%20about%20the%20house%20here%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-y